merce cunningham dance company arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe visiting artists merce cunningham dance company at stanford october 2011 hosted at stanford by dance division the inventive and innovative merce cunningham dance company will be in residence at stanford in the dance division and stanford lively arts conducting classes and workshops with stanford dance students and performing november 1 2011 about merce cunningham dance company the inventive and innovative merce cunningham dance company will be in residence at stanford in the dance division and stanford lively arts conducting classes and workshops with stanford dance students the residency will culminate in 1 an open rehearsal showing of a mini event workshop stanford dancers will dance excerpts from several of merce cunningham's works formatted as a cunningham event alastair macaulay chief dance critic of the ny times and carol teitelbaum former mcdc company member and teacher of this mini event workshop will then join in conversation about cunningham's choreography and 2 a lively arts performance of nearly 90 2009 a restaged version of cunningham's final work commissioned for the late choreographer's ninetieth birthday stanford lively arts merce cunningham visit home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
